                            <comment id="16337666" author="elyograg" created="Wed, 24 Jan 2018 14:40:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ctargett&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ctargett&quot;&gt;ctargett&lt;/a&gt; was the one who found the existing &quot;no events available&quot; message, and also found a way to fix its display.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16337718" author="ctargett" created="Wed, 24 Jan 2018 15:07:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At solr/webapp/web/partials/logging.html#L45, there is this bit of HTML:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      &amp;lt;tfoot&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;tr ng-show=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;events.length==0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
          &amp;lt;td colspan=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;4&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;No Events available&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;/tr&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;/thead&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a mismatched element (&lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;tfoot&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; closed by &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;/thead&lt;/tt&gt;), but that&apos;s not causing the problem. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In solr/webapp/web/css/angular/logging.css#L179, there is this bit of CSS:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
#content #logging #viewer .has-data tfoot
{
  display: none;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That &lt;tt&gt;.has-data&lt;/tt&gt; is a class that&apos;s given to the table in the aforementioned &lt;tt&gt;logging.html&lt;/tt&gt;, and since the &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;tfoot&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; is part of the same table, the rule says not to show the &lt;tt&gt;tfoot&lt;/tt&gt; element at all. The construct &lt;tt&gt;hasData&lt;/tt&gt; is a real JQuery function, but I can&apos;t see that it&apos;s being used here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that we could simplify this quite a bit by removing the CSS rule - in my testing removing it makes the &quot;No Events available&quot; text appear, but it disappears as soon as there is a log event to show.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also think we should remove the spinner since it indicates that something is in progress instead of what it was intended to convey, which is that a refresh is happening regularly to check for new log events.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll cook up a quick patch in a few minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16337809" author="ctargett" created="Wed, 24 Jan 2018 16:01:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached a simple patch that resolves this, and a couple of screenshots before &amp;amp; after.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I took the liberty of changing the color of the text - it was really light gray, and I thought it could benefit from a darker color (this is probably true of the UI in many other places also, but out of scope here).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
